.Enable the plugin in your projectConfiguration class

  public function setup()
  {
    $this->enablePlugins('sfDoctrinePlugin');
    $this->enablePlugins('sfRestWebServicePlugin');
  }

remember this plugin works with Doctrine.

.Enable the module in settings.yml of your app:
  enabled_modules:        [sfRestWebService]

.app yaml:
  all:
    ws:
      protected: true
      allowed: [127.0.0.1]
      protected_route: secure
      models: ~

.Allowed models
      models: ~

or
      models:
        User:
          method_for_query: ~

or
      models:
        User:
          method_for_query: findActives

.if you turn on authentication, remember to specify a secure route.
  if you have module "default" enabled, the route can be "secure" ( which is the name of the "default/secure" route )

.Edit the 500Success.php template which handles internal errors

